Press Releases.Title: 117 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 21 August 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 117 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore. Based on our investigations so far, there are 6 cases in the community, of whom 3 are Singaporeans/ Permanent Residents and 3 are Work Pass holders.

2. In addition, there are 13 imported cases, who had all been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.  

3. We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight. 


MINISTRY OF HEALTH
21 AUGUST 2020
